1
00:00:01,520 --> 00:00:05,720
THIS DRAMA IS CREATED
FOR ENTERTAINMENT PURPOSES

2
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:10,480
ALL CHARACTERS, SETTINGS
AND EVENTS ARE ENTIRELY FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:10,560 --> 00:00:15,920
THERE IS NO INTENT TO REFERENCE
ANY ORGANIZATIONS OR INDIVIDUALS

4
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,640
Then I'm opening a manhunt on Phoenix.

5
00:03:18,920 --> 00:03:22,520
They didn't just hit us where it hurts.

6
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:24,720
They tried to play superhero.

7
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:27,840
<i>They call themselves "The Seven Legends".</i>

8
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:38,600
But you have to eliminate
the Seven Legends.

9
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:40,080
Kill them all.

10
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:46,480
- Hey.
- Hey.

11
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:47,640
- Hey.
- Sarge.

12
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:49,200
You're just a mole.

13
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:49,920
Don't.

14
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:54,240
I just wanted to return the Death File.

15
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:57,080
<i>Then I'd be the loyal one.</i>

16
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:00,520
Here's the Death File, Boss.

17
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:02,320
I found it with Beauty.

18
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:07,560
She really is the mole working with Natee.

19
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:14,160
Didn't you say
she was already interrogated?

20
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:18,480
Beauty is an influencer.
A livestream queen.

21
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:20,640
She's good at luring people.

22
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:23,680
Using charm
to manipulate men is her specialty.

23
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:26,880
At first, I believed her too,
just like Arab did.

24
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:29,680
But when I checked the money trail,

25
00:04:29,760 --> 00:04:33,280
I found transfers made
to prepare an escape.

26
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:38,800
Where is Beauty now?

27
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:41,040
She got away.

28
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:44,120
I rushed to bring the Death File
back to you, so I didn't chase her.

29
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:46,920
You lived up to the trust

30
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,640
I placed in you to manage
my money-laundering network.

31
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:52,160
I will protect your interests, Boss.

32
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:55,280
I won't let them be destroyed
like Natee's or Tiangmon's.

33
00:04:58,280 --> 00:05:01,680
Send people after Beauty.

34
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:03,920
Yes, Boss.

35
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:08,120
Wait.

36
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:11,880
Yes, Boss?

37
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:15,320
Because I trust you

38
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:18,240
with the accounting systems,

39
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:22,960
I have another urgent task for you.

40
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:30,360
I want you to fly to Switzerland today

41
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:34,520
and take care of my crypto accounts there.

42
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:39,880
But Boss, aren't you about to close
an important deal at Pha Mok?

43
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:42,680
I wanted to be there to congratulate you.

44
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:47,000
Every success of mine

45
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:50,080
must have you by my side.

46
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:54,440
But the Seven Legends

47
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:58,480
destroyed both of our networks.

48
00:05:58,560 --> 00:05:59,920
I'm worried

49
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:03,160
they might hack my crypto accounts next.

50
00:06:04,080 --> 00:06:07,160
That's why I need you to handle it.

51
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:15,600
Once everything is done,

52
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,840
we'll celebrate together.

53
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:24,880
Go.

54
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:48,200
Boss,

55
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:50,680
I would never betray you.

56
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:51,640
Please let me go.

57
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:56,560
I had to go through this.

58
00:06:56,640 --> 00:06:58,440
Words alone

59
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:00,520
aren't enough anymore.

60
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:06,960
If you have proof I'm a spy,

61
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:08,280
then show me.

62
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:11,000
I can't escape anyway.

63
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:20,240
But if you're looking for a scapegoat,
don't choose me.

64
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:23,880
I've been loyal to you all along.

65
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:26,000
Shut up.

66
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:28,880
Boss is running out of patience.

67
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:33,480
I must prove whether you're really a spy.

68
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:41,000
The Seven Legends fell into my trap.

69
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:44,920
Sergeant Dab was blown to pieces.

70
00:07:45,880 --> 00:07:48,160
The rest are being hunted.

71
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,760
Once I get my hands on them,

72
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:59,760
I'll use them to prove

73
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:02,160
if you're still loyal to me.

74
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:52,360
Hey!

75
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:02,080
- Hey, I'm out of ammo.
- Hey.

76
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:04,840
- I've got nothing left, bro.
- Damn.

77
00:09:23,520 --> 00:09:26,000
Hey. Hey!

78
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:57,040
- Come on. Come on.
- Come on.

79
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:59,720
- What the hell?
- Damn it.

80
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:46,360
- Hey. What happened?
- Sorry, sorry.

81
00:11:05,920 --> 00:11:07,440
The great warrior finally shows up.

82
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:12,960
- You okay?
- Hell no.

83
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:16,600
They sent people from the whole district
to hunt us. How could we survive?

84
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,160
Hello, Moh.

85
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:29,360
I'm at the safe house now.
Who are you guys with?

86
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:33,440
I'm with Akki right now,
but he's not looking good.

87
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:35,640
Get the doctor now.

88
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:39,080
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

89
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,040
Come on.

90
00:11:46,320 --> 00:11:48,160
- Hey, they're here.
- Akki! Get him.

91
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:50,920
- How are you holding up?
- Sit down first.

92
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:52,560
- Whoa.
- Are you all right?

93
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:53,720
- Stop the bleeding first.
- How is it, bro?

94
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:56,480
- It stings like hell.
- Hold it there.

95
00:11:56,560 --> 00:11:58,840
- Press it.
- Hey, hey, hey!

96
00:11:58,920 --> 00:12:00,520
- Back off. Move aside.
- Hey.

97
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:02,160
Let me see. Let me see.

98
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:04,560
Damn, it's just a small wound.

99
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:06,280
- Such a baby. Weakling.
- Are you alright, bro?

100
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:08,240
Let's go. You there. Hey, you.

101
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:10,440
Yeah, you.

102
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:11,880
You two, take him.

103
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:13,560
- I…
- Don't talk.

104
00:12:13,640 --> 00:12:15,560
- Yeah. You wanna fight?
- Wait, I haven't said anything.

105
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:18,080
Carry him. It's nothing.
Just needs a few stitches.

106
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:21,200
- I can't help. Go.
- I'll be dead because of the doctor.

107
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:24,640
- Go with him.
- I'll go. She's gonna slap my friend.

108
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,480
Where did you even find this doctor?

109
00:12:26,560 --> 00:12:28,480
- What's wrong with her?
- Yeah.

110
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:31,120
The doctor's here now.
Akki should be fine.

111
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:34,560
That leaves Dan. No idea how he's doing.

112
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:39,360
All we can do is pray
that Mr. Dan managed to escape.

113
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:41,400
If you go out there to help now,

114
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:42,600
it's way too risky.

115
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:45,680
You're right.

116
00:12:45,760 --> 00:12:49,040
There are too many of them outside.
We need to wait for another chance.

117
00:12:49,120 --> 00:12:51,520
Damn it.
We shouldn't have fallen into their trap.

118
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:58,800
Sarge, you shouldn't have died.

119
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:00,280
Hey.

120
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:03,440
- You crazy? Don't jinx it. He isn't dead.
- Me again?

121
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:05,400
You hit harder than the doc.

122
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:06,320
Sorry.

123
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:09,040
Idiot. How could he survive that?

124
00:13:09,640 --> 00:13:11,880
He took an RPG. The explosion was massive.

125
00:13:11,960 --> 00:13:13,360
Maybe he's just insanely lucky.

126
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:15,680
And Ms. Duangnet got captured too.

127
00:13:17,680 --> 00:13:21,960
Or is this mission already
at a dead end for you guys?

128
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:44,440
Who are you?

129
00:13:48,360 --> 00:13:49,520
Hello, Mom.

130
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:51,080
Who are you calling Mom?

131
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:57,120
Mom, please calm down.

132
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:59,760
Don't be afraid of me.

133
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:04,600
I'm not a bad guy.
And I don't intend to hurt you.

134
00:14:06,560 --> 00:14:08,160
I just need a place to hide.

135
00:14:08,920 --> 00:14:13,320
From the men working for your husband.

136
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:18,440
I swear.

137
00:14:18,520 --> 00:14:21,600
I really mean no harm.

138
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:24,560
I came here because I thought

139
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:27,560
this room would be
the safest place in the hospital.

140
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:33,200
- Really?
- Yes.

141
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:37,760
Can I trust you?

142
00:14:38,280 --> 00:14:40,960
Of course. Look, isn't my smile harmless?

143
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,040
Impudent brat.

144
00:14:45,040 --> 00:14:48,200
You called me Mom.
Do you know my daughter?

145
00:14:48,280 --> 00:14:50,280
Yes. Ms. Mookda.

146
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:54,600
Then you must be Dan.

147
00:14:54,680 --> 00:14:57,400
You know me too?

148
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:03,480
Mook talks about you all the time.

149
00:15:16,760 --> 00:15:17,840
All right.

150
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:21,880
Your friend's going to be fine now.

151
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:24,760
Thank you so much, doc.

152
00:15:31,560 --> 00:15:34,520
In the end, this is all that's left of us.

153
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:37,440
Damn it. That loudmouth Sarge.

154
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:41,240
I really thought he'd finish
the mission with Ms. Duangnet.

155
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:46,840
I think Sarge did everything he could.

156
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:49,440
Doc, what do we do now?

157
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:52,920
Ms. Duangnet's been taken.

158
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:57,040
And Dan is missing.

159
00:15:57,640 --> 00:15:59,520
And we're being hunted.

160
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:02,800
We don't even know
how many of us will be left in the end.

161
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:11,800
Here's what we'll do.
You stay here and watch your friend.

162
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:14,720
Give him the meds I told you.

163
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:17,600
- Okay?
- Yes.

164
00:16:21,320 --> 00:16:22,280
Thank you.

165
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:33,320
Drop me at my condo first. I need to pack.

166
00:16:33,920 --> 00:16:36,280
Boss ordered me
to drive you straight to the airport.

167
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:37,800
He's already prepared everything.

168
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:41,760
I'm going overseas for work,
not commuting across provinces.

169
00:16:51,800 --> 00:16:53,280
This isn't the way to the airport.

170
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:54,640
Shut up.

171
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:57,280
Anyone who's no longer useful
to the Boss has to die.

172
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:19,400
No wonder Duangnet
suddenly lost contact with me.

173
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:23,319
Everyone carried out their duties
to the best of their abilities, sir.

174
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:25,000
Especially Sergeant Dab.

175
00:17:25,640 --> 00:17:29,440
He was outstanding, truly a leader
who sacrificed himself for the mission.

176
00:17:29,520 --> 00:17:31,800
If you send reinforcements now,

177
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:33,280
Ms. Duangnet might still survive.

178
00:17:33,360 --> 00:17:36,840
I can't do that. This is a secret mission.

179
00:17:36,920 --> 00:17:41,240
We don't know whether Phoenix's network
is connected to the government.

180
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:44,960
Everyone must take responsibility for
themselves and accept risks. Including me.

181
00:17:47,080 --> 00:17:49,080
I understand how you feel, sir.

182
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:51,920
But I need to wait for your orders

183
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,560
<i>on what to do next.</i>

184
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:01,600
Mission failed. Abort the operation.

185
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:04,960
Any remaining survivors are to withdraw
from the area within 24 hours.

186
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:07,800
Understood, sir.

187
00:18:13,040 --> 00:18:16,160
Sir, may I ask you something?

188
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:20,320
Are you really going to abandon a mission
that was almost successful?

189
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:25,440
When the Seven Legends and Duangnet
have already proven to us

190
00:18:25,520 --> 00:18:29,800
that they destroyed both
of Phoenix's revenue networks.

191
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:32,760
- And no one has ever achieved that before.
- Shut up.

192
00:18:32,840 --> 00:18:35,320
- But, sir.
- You do what I say.

193
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:39,040
- Sir…
- I said go.

194
00:18:39,120 --> 00:18:41,320
No matter how important
the mission for the nation is,

195
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:44,120
the lives of the Seven Legends matter too.
Everyone has parents.

196
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:45,560
Everyone has responsibilities.

197
00:18:45,640 --> 00:18:47,960
That's exactly
why you shouldn't stay silent!

198
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:50,000
I never said I would stay silent.

199
00:18:50,080 --> 00:18:52,080
I'm Captain Ong-ard's nephew.

200
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:56,200
I'm ready to give my life for the nation,
just like the Seven Legends in the past.

201
00:18:57,920 --> 00:19:01,880
Oh, sir, or…

202
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:14,320
- Mom, hello.
- Mook, hi, sweetheart.

203
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:17,520
- Come here. Let me hug you.
- Give me a hug.

204
00:19:18,640 --> 00:19:20,200
Dan, you can come out now.

205
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:24,400
Peekaboo, Ms. Mook.

206
00:19:26,760 --> 00:19:27,600
Ms. Mook.

207
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:34,920
You used me.

208
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:38,880
Mook, calm down. Let's talk this through.

209
00:19:39,920 --> 00:19:43,640
Before I called you,
I already spoke with Dan.

210
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:46,600
He had to do his duty

211
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:49,880
because your dad is a criminal.

212
00:19:52,320 --> 00:19:54,280
But he used me as bait, Mom.

213
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:02,280
You played with my feelings

214
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:05,560
just to get results?

215
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:11,520
I'm sorry.

216
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,360
I admit I approached you

217
00:20:19,040 --> 00:20:20,480
because it was my duty.

218
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:22,040
Because it was my mission.

219
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:26,160
But everything we went through,

220
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:29,240
traveling together,
the happy times together,

221
00:20:29,320 --> 00:20:30,760
that was real.

222
00:20:30,840 --> 00:20:32,320
There were no lies.

223
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:42,960
Before I was given the codename
Dan Mahittha,

224
00:20:43,960 --> 00:20:45,760
my real name was Dom.

225
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:52,320
My mission was to tear off Phoenix's mask
and wipe out their entire network.

226
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:56,320
It's a secret
I was never supposed to reveal,

227
00:20:58,040 --> 00:20:59,480
but you deserve to know.

228
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:16,120
I understand.

229
00:21:18,080 --> 00:21:21,800
Being tricked into love is painful.

230
00:21:25,040 --> 00:21:27,040
Your dad did the same to me.

231
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:31,720
But what Dan did

232
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:35,200
is different.

233
00:21:39,360 --> 00:21:40,640
He's willing to take responsibility.

234
00:21:42,120 --> 00:21:43,520
Willing to change.

235
00:21:45,920 --> 00:21:47,640
To show us that

236
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:50,720
he's still the same man.

237
00:21:51,760 --> 00:21:53,160
The man you once loved.

238
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:56,280
The man you once gave your heart to.

239
00:22:07,640 --> 00:22:11,040
I spent all my life

240
00:22:13,680 --> 00:22:15,240
trying to make your dad

241
00:22:17,520 --> 00:22:19,760
return to be…

242
00:22:21,360 --> 00:22:23,240
the man I once loved.

243
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:30,680
But I failed.

244
00:22:37,080 --> 00:22:38,600
And my time

245
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:42,760
is running out, my child.

246
00:22:44,360 --> 00:22:45,520
Mom.

247
00:22:52,080 --> 00:22:53,080
Mook.

248
00:22:56,960 --> 00:22:58,480
From now on,

249
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:03,640
the only thing I can hope for

250
00:23:05,840 --> 00:23:08,800
is you.

251
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:14,280
That you'll help your dad
become a good man again.

252
00:23:15,240 --> 00:23:17,760
Help him turn back to the right path.

253
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:23,920
Do you know, Mook?

254
00:23:26,320 --> 00:23:28,160
Your dad loves you very much.

255
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:30,840
More than anything.

256
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:38,560
Please work with Dan.

257
00:23:39,520 --> 00:23:40,400
Please.

258
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:19,040
Mr. Dan.

259
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:23,400
Mom, they're everywhere.

260
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:27,200
- Miss.
- It's all right. I'll handle it myself.

261
00:24:27,280 --> 00:24:28,840
- Get Mr. Dan out of here.
- Miss.

262
00:24:30,560 --> 00:24:32,320
Where are you going, Miss?

263
00:24:33,280 --> 00:24:36,680
My mom's been stuck in the room all day.
Can't I take her out for a walk?

264
00:24:36,760 --> 00:24:39,080
- Then let me help you.
- No need.

265
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:42,360
My mom and I already look weird enough.

266
00:24:42,440 --> 00:24:44,280
- Yes.
- What's going on?

267
00:24:46,040 --> 00:24:48,600
- Madam.
- Miss. Madam.

268
00:25:00,120 --> 00:25:04,080
- Oh my, Mook. Oh, oh. My stomach hurts.
- Mom.

269
00:25:04,160 --> 00:25:05,200
Mom.

270
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:07,280
- I can't take it anymore. It hurts.
- Madam.

271
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:10,120
- Madam. Madam.
- Mom.

272
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:11,960
Go get someone.

273
00:25:12,040 --> 00:25:13,840
- Yes.
- Ow.

274
00:25:13,920 --> 00:25:15,280
- Get me a doctor.
- Go.

275
00:25:15,360 --> 00:25:16,200
Yes.

276
00:25:18,760 --> 00:25:20,640
- Nurse.
- What's happening?

277
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:21,920
- Please help my mom.
- My stomach hurts.

278
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:23,760
Then let's go to the ER over there.

279
00:25:23,840 --> 00:25:24,920
- Yes.
- I'll help.

280
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:26,520
- Ow.
- All right.

281
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:27,840
- This way, please.
- Madam.

282
00:25:27,920 --> 00:25:29,360
- Lead the way.
- Yes.

283
00:25:53,040 --> 00:25:54,200
Ms. Mook.

284
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:58,240
How's your mom?

285
00:25:58,840 --> 00:26:02,200
My mom is an actress.
She used to be a leading lady.

286
00:26:02,800 --> 00:26:06,080
I knew it. So smooth.

287
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:08,320
- Smooth, right?
- Yeah.

288
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:10,400
But not as smooth as someone else.

289
00:26:12,840 --> 00:26:15,080
I already apologized.

290
00:26:15,680 --> 00:26:17,160
Are you still angry?

291
00:26:19,120 --> 00:26:20,400
Let me ask you honestly.

292
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:24,400
Besides you,
are there other undercover agents?

293
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:29,600
With a target this big,
you couldn't have done it alone.

294
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:35,760
Ratee.

295
00:26:36,560 --> 00:26:38,200
The one working with your father.

296
00:26:39,080 --> 00:26:42,640
She's actually the head of this operation.

297
00:26:44,400 --> 00:26:47,640
Sure. I knew it.

298
00:26:47,720 --> 00:26:50,600
No wonder she tried
to get me out of the house that day

299
00:26:51,840 --> 00:26:53,640
so you guys could chase and shoot me,

300
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:57,680
then you got to play the hero, right?

301
00:26:59,240 --> 00:27:04,080
I'm sorry. It was the only way
to get information from you.

302
00:27:07,720 --> 00:27:11,080
Ratee's real name is Duangnet.

303
00:27:11,960 --> 00:27:14,200
She had to get close to your father

304
00:27:14,280 --> 00:27:17,440
to find the real boss of Phoenix,

305
00:27:18,040 --> 00:27:19,600
the criminal network.

306
00:27:21,560 --> 00:27:24,240
But now Ms. Duangnet is under suspicion

307
00:27:24,320 --> 00:27:26,080
and has been captured by your father.

308
00:27:26,840 --> 00:27:30,880
So we had to change our main mission
to rescuing her instead.

309
00:27:37,200 --> 00:27:40,320
Then I'll help you.

310
00:27:42,480 --> 00:27:46,040
I think I know
where my father is holding Ms. Duangnet.

311
00:27:49,160 --> 00:27:50,240
Thank you.

312
00:27:57,800 --> 00:27:59,200
Hey, stop right there!

313
00:27:59,280 --> 00:28:00,840
- Hurry, Ms. Mook.
- Mr. Dan.

314
00:28:02,640 --> 00:28:03,880
Mr. Dan!

315
00:28:20,720 --> 00:28:23,120
Your father was right about one thing.

316
00:28:23,640 --> 00:28:25,560
You showed us exactly who the spy is.

317
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:30,280
Ms. Mook!

318
00:28:32,800 --> 00:28:33,720
Mr. Dan.

319
00:29:30,240 --> 00:29:32,280
No. Don't kill him.

320
00:29:34,280 --> 00:29:35,600
I won't kill him now.

321
00:29:36,120 --> 00:29:38,120
I'll let your father kill him
in front of you.

322
00:29:38,640 --> 00:29:40,360
- Hey, go get Ms. Mookda.
- Hey.

323
00:29:40,440 --> 00:29:42,160
- Yes, sir.
- Let me go.

324
00:29:42,760 --> 00:29:44,000
- Come here.
- Let go.

325
00:29:44,080 --> 00:29:46,000
- Let go.
- Come here. Get up.

326
00:29:54,320 --> 00:29:55,960
Hey, let go.

327
00:30:03,080 --> 00:30:05,240
Dad. Dad.

328
00:30:05,320 --> 00:30:07,240
Dad. That's enough. Please.

329
00:30:07,320 --> 00:30:09,880
Ms. Dan. Dad, please don't hurt him.

330
00:30:09,960 --> 00:30:11,120
Mr. Dan.

331
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:19,960
- I told you not to cause trouble again.
- Go ahead then. Do it.

332
00:30:21,720 --> 00:30:23,600
So Mom and I can finally give up

333
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:25,920
on the idea that you'll ever change.

334
00:30:26,680 --> 00:30:28,520
- Take Mook away!
- Dad.

335
00:30:29,520 --> 00:30:30,760
- Dad.
- Hey.

336
00:30:30,840 --> 00:30:32,560
- Don't. I said don't.
- I'm begging you.

337
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:33,640
- Let Ms. Mook go.
- Let go.

338
00:30:33,720 --> 00:30:34,920
- Go. Go.
- Dad please.

339
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:37,120
- Don't hurt Mr. Dan, please, Dad.
- Go.

340
00:30:37,200 --> 00:30:39,560
- Let go! Ms. Mook!
- Let go! Mr. Dan!

341
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:46,160
Finally, I've got my hands
on one of the Seven Legends.

342
00:30:48,800 --> 00:30:50,240
Interrogate him.

343
00:30:50,760 --> 00:30:52,680
Find out where the rest of them are.

344
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:55,560
You're good at giving orders.
What have you actually done?

345
00:30:57,240 --> 00:30:59,520
I need to check
on the people handling Praewpan.

346
00:31:00,200 --> 00:31:01,320
I'll go see.

347
00:31:06,040 --> 00:31:07,200
Let me go.

348
00:31:08,880 --> 00:31:10,440
Seven Legends?

349
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:13,000
Seven Legends?

350
00:31:13,080 --> 00:31:14,120
- Ow.
- Hey.

351
00:31:14,200 --> 00:31:16,680
This time, you'll spill everything.

352
00:31:21,360 --> 00:31:22,200
Hey.

353
00:31:26,200 --> 00:31:27,280
The hell's going on?

354
00:31:33,800 --> 00:31:34,880
Where am I?

355
00:31:36,800 --> 00:31:37,880
Hey.

356
00:31:54,720 --> 00:31:56,840
<i>Then I'm opening a manhunt on Phoenix</i>

357
00:31:57,440 --> 00:31:59,680
to bring Ms. Duangnet back.

358
00:32:00,280 --> 00:32:01,440
I'll show you my trick shot.

359
00:32:16,960 --> 00:32:19,040
I never should've taken this job.

360
00:32:36,320 --> 00:32:39,640
Praew… pan.

361
00:32:47,680 --> 00:32:49,440
Same old habits, Sarge.

362
00:32:53,120 --> 00:32:54,800
Always disappearing without a word.

363
00:32:55,480 --> 00:32:57,040
Not even a thank you.

364
00:33:06,960 --> 00:33:08,160
That's Phoenix's victim.

365
00:33:23,360 --> 00:33:24,240
Praew.

366
00:33:25,560 --> 00:33:26,600
Are you hurt?

367
00:33:30,960 --> 00:33:32,840
Phoenix doesn't need me anymore.

368
00:33:32,920 --> 00:33:35,680
So they're silencing
anyone who's no longer useful.

369
00:33:39,720 --> 00:33:40,880
You were shot.

370
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:44,560
You need to go to the hospital.

371
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:49,840
Even you are being hunted.
If I show up there, I won't survive.

372
00:33:50,440 --> 00:33:53,520
- But if we leave it like this…
- I don't die easily, Sarge.

373
00:33:53,600 --> 00:33:55,400
I worked for Phoenix.

374
00:33:55,480 --> 00:33:57,280
I know how to survive.

375
00:33:59,040 --> 00:34:00,000
Praew.

376
00:34:01,440 --> 00:34:05,280
Go see a doctor.
I know a doctor who can help you.

377
00:34:06,560 --> 00:34:09,520
Help me, so we're even?

378
00:34:09,600 --> 00:34:11,480
So we don't owe each other
anything anymore?

379
00:34:11,560 --> 00:34:13,400
Stop being sarcastic.

380
00:34:14,639 --> 00:34:17,000
You came to help me. You betrayed them.

381
00:34:18,360 --> 00:34:20,480
Now I know that the kid I once saved…

382
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:23,440
is back.

383
00:34:25,840 --> 00:34:28,520
Sarge, believe me.

384
00:34:29,520 --> 00:34:32,120
Right now, you can't beat Phoenix.

385
00:34:33,320 --> 00:34:34,199
Why?

386
00:34:34,719 --> 00:34:39,320
Phoenix is working with a mafia group

387
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:40,960
that trades military-grade weapons.

388
00:34:41,840 --> 00:34:43,639
Their goal

389
00:34:43,719 --> 00:34:48,400
is to use Pha Mok as a hub
to sell weapons to terrorists.

390
00:34:49,280 --> 00:34:50,719
Terrorists?

391
00:34:52,239 --> 00:34:54,320
They want to dominate the region.

392
00:34:54,960 --> 00:34:57,000
That's why
they reset their entire network.

393
00:34:58,120 --> 00:35:00,560
Once I knew too much,

394
00:35:00,640 --> 00:35:02,320
they tried to get rid of me.

395
00:35:04,200 --> 00:35:05,280
Phoenix.

396
00:35:06,720 --> 00:35:08,920
It really isn't just cybercrime.

397
00:35:10,360 --> 00:35:13,160
It's good you know now.
So we can clip their wings.

398
00:35:13,240 --> 00:35:14,400
Sarge.

399
00:35:15,560 --> 00:35:17,440
Don't throw your life away here.

400
00:35:18,920 --> 00:35:20,120
I can't, Praew.

401
00:35:21,360 --> 00:35:24,000
I won't let Phoenix destroy my country.

402
00:35:25,720 --> 00:35:30,400
Praew, you have to tell me
who Phoenix really is.

403
00:35:30,480 --> 00:35:32,160
We'll deal with them.

404
00:35:32,800 --> 00:35:35,600
And you'll be protected as a witness.

405
00:35:35,680 --> 00:35:37,200
You won't be held responsible.

406
00:35:53,280 --> 00:35:56,480
That's Phoenix true identity?

407
00:35:59,520 --> 00:36:01,120
I never expected it.

408
00:36:02,600 --> 00:36:04,160
That bastard.

409
00:36:14,160 --> 00:36:15,160
Hey.

410
00:36:20,120 --> 00:36:21,400
His name is Dan.

411
00:36:22,920 --> 00:36:24,880
He's one of the Seven Legends.

412
00:36:25,640 --> 00:36:27,440
We captured him for interrogation,

413
00:36:27,520 --> 00:36:30,760
but he won't tell us where the others are.

414
00:36:33,720 --> 00:36:35,880
So? Do you know him?

415
00:36:41,520 --> 00:36:42,920
Okay.

416
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:46,280
It's time for you to prove your loyalty

417
00:36:47,520 --> 00:36:49,440
and show that you're not a mole.

418
00:36:59,760 --> 00:37:00,920
Ratee.

419
00:37:03,520 --> 00:37:05,480
Please shoot him in the head for me.

420
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:10,520
Prove your loyalty to me.

421
00:37:14,720 --> 00:37:15,560
Now.

422
00:37:29,760 --> 00:37:32,600
You said you weren't a mole.

423
00:37:32,680 --> 00:37:35,400
This is your chance to prove it.

424
00:37:36,200 --> 00:37:38,160
Just blow his head off.

425
00:37:38,240 --> 00:37:41,120
That's all it takes
to show me you're not a mole.

426
00:37:44,760 --> 00:37:45,760
Shoot him.

427
00:37:47,920 --> 00:37:49,320
Shoot him for me.

428
00:37:50,960 --> 00:37:52,320
Shoot!

429
00:38:04,880 --> 00:38:08,200
So they want you to trade the lives
of the Seven Legends for Ms. Duangnet?

430
00:38:10,200 --> 00:38:11,960
- Go.
- Hey. What?

431
00:38:12,040 --> 00:38:13,960
- Sit down.
- Hey, hey.

432
00:38:14,040 --> 00:38:15,200
<i>Right now,</i>

433
00:38:15,280 --> 00:38:18,160
<i>there's unusual movement</i>
<i>along the border on the other side.</i>

434
00:38:18,240 --> 00:38:21,920
<i>So they want us to focus only</i>
<i>on our own lives and Ms. Duangnet's</i>

435
00:38:22,480 --> 00:38:24,880
and not interfere with a larger objective.

436
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:31,040
Take cover, Ms. Duangnet.

437
00:38:31,120 --> 00:38:35,680
<i>That means we must stop</i>
<i>this major weapons deal from happening.</i>

438
00:38:36,920 --> 00:38:39,920
<i>You have four hours</i>
<i>to cross over and take down Phoenix.</i>

439
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:01,680
‪Why are you running?!

440
00:39:01,760 --> 00:39:02,600
‪Hey!

441
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:20,840
Go!

442
00:39:29,880 --> 00:39:32,360
- Cut. Okay. Come on.
- Come.

443
00:39:32,440 --> 00:39:34,560
Get it ready. Get in place.

444
00:39:34,640 --> 00:39:35,720
That's it. Just like that.

445
00:39:35,800 --> 00:39:37,920
Look at the mark. Imagine it's coming.

446
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:40,720
Shoot. Bang, bang!

447
00:39:40,800 --> 00:39:42,520
Get down. Out of ammo.

448
00:39:42,600 --> 00:39:43,800
Oh? What now?

449
00:39:43,880 --> 00:39:44,720
‪Hey.

450
00:39:44,800 --> 00:39:45,720
Turn back.

451
00:39:56,720 --> 00:39:58,520
- I'm out of ammo.
- I've got nothing left, bro.

452
00:40:01,520 --> 00:40:02,360
Hey.

453
00:40:11,200 --> 00:40:13,280
- Hey, I really like you.
- Come on.

454
00:40:27,960 --> 00:40:28,920
Let go!

455
00:40:41,760 --> 00:40:44,320
Enough. Cut.

456
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:50,320
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
